  "content": "# Task Objective\nAnalyze the provided sales and warehouse data to generate a clear summary and visualize key findings through at least one generated figure.\n\n# Input Dataset Summary\nThe analysis will be performed on the file `Warehouse_and_Retail_Sales.csv`.\n*   **Rows:** 307,645\n*   **Columns:** `YEAR`, `MONTH`, `SUPPLIER`, `ITEM CODE`, `ITEM DESCRIPTION`, `ITEM TYPE`, `RETAIL SALES`, `RETAIL TRANSFERS`, `WAREHOUSE SALES`.\n*   **Data Types:** Numerical fields (`RETAIL SALES`, `RETAIL TRANSFERS`, `WAREHOUSE SALES`) are floats. Temporal and categorical fields are integers or strings.\n\n# Assumptions From Schema\n1.  The dataset contains historical sales and inventory movement data across different years and months.\n2.  `RETAIL SALES`, `RETAIL TRANSFERS`, and `WAREHOUSE SALES` are quantifiable numeric metrics suitable for aggregation and visualization.\n3.  The temporal fields (`YEAR`, `MONTH`) can be used for time-series analysis.\n4.  The goal of the analysis is to identify meaningful relationships between sales, transfers, and warehouse figures, potentially segmented by supplier or item type.\n\n# Required Outputs\n1.  A clear textual summary of the dataset's key findings.\n2.  At least one generated visualization (figure) that effectively explains a significant relationship or trend found in the data.\n\n# Code Constraints\n1.  **File Structure:** Generated code must be distributed across `data_loader.py`, `preprocessing.py`, `analysis.py`, and `figures.py`.\n2.  **Libraries:** Only the `pandas` and `matplotlib` libraries are permitted for computation and visualization.\n3.  **Execution Environment:** No external network access or shell commands are allowed.\n4.  **Logic:** All analytical logic must be explicit and highly readable.",
